                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract1410-1">In hagiography: <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1410">Pethion</persName> was a 
                        Zoroastrian convert who, with his uncle the monk <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1520">Yazdin</persName>, preached 
                        in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/121">the region of the lower Zab</placeName>. His hagiography was connected 
                        to that of an aristocratic father and daughter pair whom he helped to convert:<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1119">Adorhormizd</persName> and 
                        his daughter <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1129">Anahid</persName>. Pethion was martyred under <persName>Yazdegerd II</persName>.</note>
